{"parse":{"title":"Teldrassil","pageid":14039,"wikitext":{"*":":''{{text|yellow|Note:}} For characters 110 and above, by default Teldrassil will be inaccessible and viewable only from a distance (unless they go back in time via {{NPC||Zidormi}}). For characters below 110, Teldrassil appears as it did before the {{b-inline}} [[War of the Thorns]].''\n{{Wow-article}}\n{{Infobox zone\n|faction=Alliance\n|name=Teldrassil\n|level=Scalable 1-20\n|ss=Teldrassil_Concept.jpg\n|caption=A view of Teldrassil.\n|capital=[[Darnassus]] (15,000)\n|pop=23,962\n|races={{Race|Night elf}} (20,400)<br />{{Race|Furbolg}} (1,440)<br />{{Race|Dryad}} (1,200)<br />{{Race|Human}} (720)<br />{{Race|Harpy }} (180)<br />{{Race|Satyr }} (22)<br />{{Race|High Elf}} (?)\n|government=Elected council\n|rulers=High Priestess {{npc||Tyrande Whisperwind}}<br />\nArchdruid {{npc||Malfurion Stormrage}}\nArchdruid {{npc||Fandral Staghelm}} (Former)\n|major=[[Darnassus]] (15,000)<br />\n[[Dolanaar]] (5,000)<br />\n[[Aldrassil]] (2,000)\n|minor=[[Rut'theran Village]] (300)\n|languages=[[Darnassian]], [[Common]], [[Ursine]]\n|faiths=[[Ancients]], [[druidism]], [[Elune]]\n|resources=[[Gold]], [[hunting]], [[leather]], [[timber]]\n|affiliation=[[Alliance]]\n|loc=[[The Veiled Sea]] / [[Northern Kalimdor]]\n|source=''[[Lands of Mystery]]'', pg. 20\n}}\n[[File:Teldrassil.jpg|thumb|Teldrassil in the game]]\n'''Teldrassil''' is an island and [[great tree]] off [[Kalimdor]]'s northern coast.<ref name=\"Lands of Mystery 20\">''[[Lands of Mystery]]'', pg. 20</ref> It was the home of the reclusive [[night elves]] and a stunning testament to the power of their magic and connection with nature.\n\nThe night elves moved their [[capital]] to an island off northwest Kalimdor.<ref name=\"World of Warcraft The Roleplaying Game 19\">''[[World of Warcraft The Roleplaying Game]]'', pg. 19</ref> It was here that the [[Circle of the Ancients]] and the wise [[druid]]s pooled their power to create another [[World Tree]], but on a smaller scale. They called this tree Teldrassil (\"crown of the earth\") and built their city of [[Darnassus]] in its branches. The island takes the name of the \"tree\" as well, and a twilit forest covered it.<ref name=\"World of Warcraft The Roleplaying Game 19\">''[[World of Warcraft The Roleplaying Game]]'', pg. 19</ref>\n\nTeldrassil is truly massive, a huge trunk rising out of the sea and holding the entire night elf homeland, and the capital of [[Darnassus]], in its boughs. The enterprise was not blessed by all of the [[Dragon Aspect|Aspects]], unlike its predecessor. Regardless, the behemoth of a tree dwarfs [[Nordrassil]], large enough that a decent amount of land emerged atop its gargantuan limbs. Trees, flora, and fauna were spread across the magical tree.\n\n== History ==\nAfter the cataclysmic events that followed the [[Third War|invasion]] of the [[Burning Legion]], {{npc||Malfurion Stormrage||Malfurion}} went missing. Archdruid {{npc||Fandral Staghelm}} took over the leadership of the night elven druids, convincing the Circle of the Ancients in [[Darkshore]] that it was time for the night elven people to rebuild the World Tree and regain their cherished immortality. However, his plan failed due to the fact that {{npc||Nozdormu}}, the source of the night elves immortality, did not bless the tree.\n\nThe Circle of the Ancients and powerful druids combined their powers to grow an immense tree in the [[Veiled Sea]]. They called the tree Teldrassil, meaning \"crown of the earth\" in [[Darnassian]]. The night elves made their new home in the boughs of Teldrassil, creating a forest of mighty trees and flowing rivers, bathed in the endless night that fell over the lands of the elves from the dawn of time.\n\nHowever, the calm of the enchanted forest has slowly fallen into the shadow of a sinister presence. Crazed [[furbolg]]s, [[satyr]]s and fouler beasts have appeared in Teldrassil, occupying all the attention of the vigilant [[Sentinel]]s and the wise [[druid]]s to ensure the safety of their new home. The source of this corruption remained a mystery for some time, until the conflict of the [[Emerald Nightmare]] spilled into the waking world.\n\nMalfurion, upon returning to Darnassus, discovered that a remnant of a great evil he had sealed away had attached itself to Teldrassil. This corrupted the tree and drove it mad, spreading its evil to everything around it. The archdruid managed to remove this parasite, and eventually restored the tree to what it once was. {{npc||Alexstrasza}}, impressed that the tree could prosper alone without her influence or her kin's, blessed it belatedly. The tree flourishes even more under the gift from the Life-Binder, even if still being unable to return the night elves' immortality.\n\n== In Cataclysm ==\n{{Cata-section}}\nThe [[Gnarlpine]] [[furbolg]] became corrupted due to [[Ursal the Mauler|Ursal the Mauler's]] use of fel moss.\n\n== In Battle for Azeroth ==\n{{Battle-section}}\nDuring the [[War of the Thorns]], in an attempt to strike a devastating blow to the Alliance, [[Sylvanas Windrunner]] and the [[Horde]] pushed through [[Ashenvale]] to lay siege to Teldrassil from the shores of [[Darkshore]]. After hearing word of [[Malfurion Stormrage]]'s survival, she chose to cover Teldrassil in flame instead of capturing it, killing all those trapped civilians within that could not escape in time to the water or through portals to [[Stormwind City]]. After the burning, Teldrassil is largely uninhabited and [[Darnassus]] is destroyed.\n\n== Geography ==\nFor characters below 110, the majority of Teldrassil's upper reaches is open forest and it resembles a mid-sized forested island. [[Darnassus]] takes up a large chunk on the western side of this island, while the smaller cities of [[Aldrassil]] and [[Dolanaar]] dot the remaining forest. All forms of terrain exist here, including streams, full-sized lakes, and a few hills that might be considered mountains.<ref name=\"Lands of Mystery 20\">''[[Lands of Mystery]]'', pg. 20</ref>\n\nThe entire [[zone]] of Teldrassil is in fact one huge tree, grown on an island off the coast of [[Kalimdor]]. As such, there are no [[ore]] deposits to speak of here and the night elves are not known as crafty [[blacksmith]]s or [[miner]]s. However, because the tree is so full of life, [[herb]]s are numerous.\n\nAlthough Teldrassil is only the size of a mid-sized island in width, its sheer height rivals any other island. It has been described as an \"island continent\".<ref name=\"World of Warcraft The Roleplaying Game 38\">''[[World of Warcraft The Roleplaying Game]]'', pg. 38</ref> Another reference in the book<ref name=\"World of Warcraft The Roleplaying Game 19\">''[[World of Warcraft The Roleplaying Game]]'', pg. 19</ref> and other sources simply call it an island.\n\nTeldrassil contains no [[dungeon]]s, [[raid dungeon]]s, [[micro dungeon]]s, or [[battleground]]s. It is the starting area for the [[night elf|night elves]] and contains a very sheltered 1-5 leveling area, [[Shadowglen]]. The night elf [[capital city]] of [[Darnassus]] can also be found in this zone, though the travel hub is actually located at [[Rut'theran Village]] (accessible by portal from Darnassus).\n\n=== Effects of the Cataclysm ===\n{{Cata-section}}\n\nTeldrassil escaped the Cataclysm virtually unscathed, with the major exception of the shattering of [[Rut'theran Village]]. It has now been split from the mainland and exists as its own island. The boat routes from the destroyed port town of [[Auberdine]] in [[Darkshore]] have also been relocated here, so now there are three docks (one unused) on the island.\n\n=== Effects of the War of the Thorns ===\n{{Battle-section}}\nFor characters who have achieved at least level 110, Teldrassil will be engulfed in flames. It has been completely removed from the game world, and thus inaccessible by flying, swimming, or any other means, such as {{ability|Eagle Eye}}. A marker for the [[Remains of Darnassus]] will appear on the map, but only as a reference.\n\n{{NPC||Zidormi}} can be found near the main north to south road in Darkshore, however, and is able to take players back in time to before the tree was attacked if they wish to visit.\n\n== Travel ==\n{{Wow-section}}\n:''{{Text|yellow|Note:}} all these travel methods are only available for players when the zone is in the pre-{{battle-inline}} state.''\n=== Getting there ===\n[[File:Gryphon.png|right|Gryphon]]\nHead to north Darkshore. Go to the [[Ruins of Mathystra]]. Use an [[Elixir of Water Walking]] (or similar class ability) and have a fast land mount. Ride out towards [[Teldrassil]] and look for a good place to start your ride. The fatigue zone has an irregular shape. Generally a north or northwest course across the fatigue zone will work. Ride towards the island, which you should be able to see. You have 60 seconds to complete the crossing. You will see [[Rut'theran Village]] when you arrive there.\n\n=== Flight Master locations ===\n:{{Alliance}} [[Darnassus]]\n:{{Alliance}} [[Dolanaar]]\n:{{Alliance}} [[Rut'theran Village]]\n\n=== Boat locations ===\n:{{Alliance}} [[Rut'theran Village]] (west dock - [[Azuremyst Isle]]; south dock - [[Stormwind Harbor]])\n\n=== Portals ===\n:{{Alliance}} [[Rut'theran Village]] (to [[Darnassus]])\n:{{Alliance}} [[Darnassus]] (west) (to [[Rut'theran Village]])\n:{{Alliance}} [[Darnassus]] ([[Temple of the Moon]]) (to [[Stair of Destiny]] or [[Exodar]])\n\n=== Adjacent regions ===\n{| class=\"darktable\"\n|-\n! Zone Name !! Faction !! Level Range !! Direction !! {{Alliance}} Access !! {{Horde}} Access\n|-\n| [[Azuremyst Isle]] || {{Alliance}}\n| 1-10 || Southwest\n| By boat from [[Rut'theran Village]] to [[Valaar's Berth]]; [[File:MiniIcon FlightMaster.png]] from [[Rut'theran Village]] to [[Exodar]]; portal from [[Darnassus]] to [[Exodar]]\n| By boat from [[Rut'theran Village]] to [[Valaar's Berth]] ('''Alliance vessel''')\n|-class=\"alt\"\n| [[Bloodmyst Isle]] || {{Alliance}}\n| 10-20 || Southwest\n| By boat, flight, or portal to [[Azuremyst Isle]] (see above), then [[File:MiniIcon FlightMaster.png]] from [[Exodar]] to [[Blood Watch]]\n| By boat to [[Azuremyst Isle]] (see above), then by foot north\n|-\n| [[Darkshore]] || {{Alliance}}\n| 10-20 || Southeast\n| Swim using speed and health potions; Flying mount; [[File:MiniIcon FlightMaster.png]] from [[Rut'theran Village]] to [[Lor'danel]]\n| Swim using speed and health potions; Flying mount\n|}\n\n== Inhabitants ==\n:''{{Text|yellow|Note:}} all these inhabitants are only seen when the zone is in the pre-{{battle-inline}} state.''\n[[File:Beasts.png|right]]\n{| class=\"darktable\"\n|-\n! Classification !! Type\n|-\n| rowspan=\"4\"| [[Beast]]\n| [[Boar]]s\n|-\n| [[Nightsaber]]s\n|-\n| [[Owl]]s\n|-\n| [[Spider]]s\n|-class=\"alt\"\n| rowspan=\"1\" | [[Demon]]\n| [[Satyr]]\n|-\n| rowspan=\"1\" | [[Elemental]]\n| [[Timberling]]s\n|-class=\"alt\"\n| rowspan=\"4\"| [[Humanoid]]\n| [[Furbolg]]s\n|-class=\"alt\"\n| [[Grell]]s\n|-class=\"alt\"\n| [[Harpy|Harpies]]\n|-class=\"alt\"\n| [[Worgen]]\n|}\n\n== Resources ==\n:''{{Text|yellow|Note:}} all these resources are only available for players when the zone is in the pre-{{battle-inline}} state.''\n[[File:Trade herbalism.png|right]]\n[[File:Inv misc pelt wolf 01.png|right]]\n[[File:Trade fishing.png|right]]\n{| class=\"darktable\"\n|-\n! Source !! Item !! Skill Level\n|-\n| rowspan=\"4\"| [[Herbalism]]\n| {{item|icon=|Peacebloom}}\n| align=\"center\" | 1\n|-\n| {{item|icon=|Silverleaf}}\n| align=\"center\" | 1\n|-\n| {{item|icon=|Earthroot}}\n| align=\"center\" | 15\n|-\n| {{item|icon=|Mageroyal}}\n| align=\"center\" | 50\n|}\n{| class=\"darktable\"\n|-\n! Source !! Item\n|-\n| rowspan=\"1\"| [[Cloth]] (Drop)\n| {{item|icon=|Linen Cloth}}\n|-class=\"alt\"\n| rowspan=\"3\" | [[Skinning]]\n| {{item|icon=|Ruined Leather Scraps}}\n|-class=\"alt\"\n| {{item|icon=|Light Leather}}\n|-class=\"alt\"\n| {{item|icon=|Light Hide}}\n|}\n\n''Note: Though there are no pools, the waters in and around Teldrassil can be fished successfully with a minimum skill of 25.''{{fact}}\n\n== Notable characters ==\n{{Wow-section}}\n:''{{Text|yellow|Note:}} all these characters are only available for players when the zone is in the pre-{{battle-inline}} state.''\n{{main|Teldrassil NPCs}}\nTeldrassil is home to several night elves of status. From the top of the tree [[Aldrassil]], {{npc||Tenaron Stormgrip}} sends promising young elves out into the outside world. In [[Dolanaar]], {{npc||Tallonkai Swiftroot}} leads the effort to fight back the corrupted furbolgs and satyr of the Great Tree, while in his small tent near [[Lake Al'Ameth]], {{npc||Denalan}} seeks to understand the nature of the strange affliction, seeping into Teldrassil.\n\n== Quests ==\n{{Cata-section}}\n:''{{Text|yellow|Note:}} all these quests are only available for players when the zone is in the pre-{{battle-inline}} state.''\n[[File:Quest point.png|right]]\n{{main|Teldrassil quests}}\n\n{{seealso|Teldrassil questing guide}}\nThe first quests are simple, like in every other starting zone.\n\nOne of the most important quests for new night elf adventurers in Teldrassil is the {{quest|Crown of the Earth|Crown of the Earth}} quest chain. In this chain, night elves are sent to gather [[water]] from [[moonwell]]s scattered all over the island. Each time they return with the moonwell water, they learn a little more of the night elf history. Other important quests include the {{quest|Denalan's Earth|Timberling}} quest chain, in which adventurers must help investigate a corruption of the [[timberling]]s of Teldrassil, and the {{quest|A Troubling Breeze|Furbolg}} chain, which deals with the corruption of the local [[furbolg]] population.\n\n== Areas of interest ==\n{{Wow-section}}\n:''{{Text|yellow|Note:}} all these areas are only available for players when the zone is in the pre-{{battle-inline}} state.''\n[[File:Inv misc idol 05.png|right]]\n=== Maps ===\n<gallery>\nFile:WorldMap-Teldrassil-old.jpg|Teldrassil pre-Cataclysm\nFile:WorldMap-Teldrassil.jpg|Teldrassil post-Cataclysm (current)\n</gallery>\n\n=== PvP ===\nTeldrassil sees very little [[PvP]] action due to the fact that [[Horde]] players have to cross through [[Rut'Theran Village]] and Darnassus. The only way for Horde players to get to Teldrassil itself is via ship from [[Auberdine]] (also Night-Elf controlled) on mainland Kalimdor. Most other [[starting area]]s are directly accessible by the opposing faction without such hazards.\n\n=== Subzones ===\n{| class=\"darktable\"\n|-\n!{{wow-inline}} In-game\n|-\n|{{Teldrassil|subzonesonly=}}\n|}\n\n== Media ==\n=== Images ===\n;Pre-War of the Thorns\n<gallery position=\"center\" captionalign=\"center\">\nFile:Teldrassilmovie.jpg|Teldrassil from [[Warcraft (film)|Warcraft]].\nFile:Teldrassilcomic.jpg|Teldrassil from the comic.\nFile:Teldrassilcomic2.jpg|Teldrassil from the comic.\nFile:Idrassil.jpeg|[[Idrassil]], a possible concept for Teldrassil.\nFile:Teldrassil 070910 015837 - Darnassus - Kirkburn 12319.jpg|Darnassus bank from the air.\nFile:Teldrassil1.jpg|A Teldrassil glade.\nFile:Gnarlpine Hold.jpg|Gnarlpine Hold\nFile:Teldrassil 070910 020014 - Rut'theran - Kirkburn 12319.jpg|Rut'theran Village, post-Cataclysm\n</gallery>\n\n;During and after War of the Thorns\n<gallery position=\"center\" captionalign=\"center\">\nBattle for Azeroth - Horde advance on Teldrassil.jpg|The Horde advance on Teldrassil during the {{b-inline}} [[War of the Thorns]]\nBattle for Azeroth - Teldrassil burning art.jpg|{{b-inline}} Teldrassil burning\nBattle for Azeroth - Teldrassil burning.png|{{b-inline}} Teldrassil burning, as seen from Darkshore\nFile:Teldrassil_burning_from_Darkshore.jpg|{{b-inline}} Teldrassil burning, as seen from Darkshore in-game\nFile:Teldrassil_burning_from_Darkshore_closer.jpg|{{b-inline}} closer view of Teldrassil burning in-game\n</gallery>\n\n=== Videos ===\n{{Outdated-section|Needs video about [[War of the Thorns]] and later.}}\n<gallery captionalign=\"center\" position=\"center\">\nFile:Teldrassil Storyline with Fun Lore Facts in World of Warcraft 4K\nFile:Cataclysm - Teldrassil Overview\n</gallery>\n\n== Notes ==\n:''{{Text|yellow|Note:}} most of this info only applies when the zone is in the pre-{{battle-inline}} state.''\n[[File:Trade_archaeology_highborne_scroll.png|right]]\n* At the tree's base there are some pieces of wooded land between its roots, one of which has an abandoned furbolg house on it, as well as [[Rut'theran Village]].\n\n* While Teldrassil looks like a baobab with a thick trunk in ''World of Warcraft'' (its branches can't be seen), it looks more like a regular tree in art, and will resemble such in [[Warcraft (film)|Warcraft]]. The possible reason it looks like this in-game is because the engine is based completely off height-mapping, which heavily limits terrain possibilities. The map for Darnassus in ''Cataclysm'' seems to imply that Teldrassil is a stump.\n\n*[[Blizzard Entertainment|Blizzard]] originally said the name of the island where Teldrassil was grown was named [[Kalidar]] on a preview website. It was also seen as Kalidar in the World of Warcraft DVD.\n\n== Trivia ==\n*Teldrassil's name, like that of Nordrassil, is probably taken from \"Yggdrasil\", the World Ash tree of Norse mythology.\n*If you go to the highest point of Teldrassil with a Flying Mount and Dismount, you will be fall for 30-40 seconds before you land...Try this ONLY OVER WATER unless you want to pay for repairs.\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n;Pre-War of the Thorns\n{{elinks-zone|141}}\n\n\n{{Kalimdor}}\n\n[[de:Teldrassil]]\n[[es:Teldrassil]]\n[[fr:Teldrassil]]\n[[it:Teldrassil]]\n[[nl:Teldrassil]]\n[[pl:Teldrassil]]\n[[sk:Teldrassil]]\n[[ru:\u0422\u0435\u043b\u044c\u0434\u0440\u0430\u0441\u0441\u0438\u043b]]\n[[Category:Islands]]\n[[Category:Nations]]\n[[Category:Night elf territories]]\n[[Category:Starting areas]]\n[[Category:Teldrassil| ]]\n[[Category:Trees]]"}}}